---
layout: base.njk
title: The Workbench
eleventyExcludeFromCollections: true
description: Thoughts on bespoke web design, hard-coded performance, and taking on the bloated templates.
---

<div class="blog-roll">
  <h1>The Workbench</h1>
  <p class="blog-summary" style="font-size: 1.25rem; margin-bottom: 3.5rem;">
    Thoughts on bespoke web design, hard-coded performance, and why I build everything from scratch in Pembrokeshire.
  </p>

  <ul class="blog-list">
  {%- for post in collections.blog | reverse -%}
    <li class="blog-item article-preview">
      {%- set preview_img = post.data.thumb_image | default(post.data.hero_image) -%}
      {%- if preview_img -%}
      <div class="article-preview-thumb">
        <a href="{{ post.url }}">
          <img src="{{ preview_img }}" alt="{{ post.data.image_alt | default('Thumbnail for ' ~ post.data.title) }}" style="object-fit: cover; width: 100%; height: 100%;" />
        </a>
      </div>
      {%- endif -%}

      <div class="article-preview-content">
        <div class="blog-meta-row">
          <span class="blog-author-highlight">BY JAMES</span>
          <span>&bull;</span>
          <span class="blog-date" style="margin: 0;">{{ post.date | dateReadable }}</span>
          <span>&bull;</span>
          <span class="blog-reading-time">{{ post.content | readingTime }}</span>
        </div>
        <h2 class="blog-title"><a href="{{ post.url }}">{{ post.data.title | default(post.fileSlug) }}</a></h2>
        <p class="blog-summary">
          {{ post.data.description | default("Read article &rarr;" | safe) }}
        </p>
      </div>
    </li>
  {%- endfor -%}
  </ul>
</div>

